        "subject": "LU-00000 ptlrpc: Avoid mutex in sec gc list",
        "message": "LU-00000 ptlrpc: Avoid mutex in sec gc list\n\nCall chains originating from lnet_finalize must not sleep.\nsptlrpc_gc_del_sec is using a mutex for synchronization that\ncan be rewritten by including including the sec_cop_destroy_sec\ncall and re-working the sec_do_gc workqueue logic to avoid the\nuse of a mutex.\n\nlnet_finalize\n -> spin_lock()\n    lnet_eq_enqueue_event()\n     -> ptlrpc_master_callback()\n       -> request_out_callback()\n         -> ptlrpc_req_finished()\n           -> __ptlrpc_req_finished()\n             -> sptlrpc_req_put_ctx()\n               -> gss_sec_release_ctx_kr()\n                 -> sptlrpc_sec_put\n                   -> sptlrpc_gc_del_sec <- avoid mutex here\n <- spin_unlock()\n\nSigned-off-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ia440d47c9696abc280965560350447ca9248858d\n"
      },
